The couplet in English is:

Pious man wears new color, friend's wealth flows like a river; 
Five locks of hair wander abroad, drinking wine and indulging in many pleasures.

Cupid's quiver full of grief in the Kalikalam,
Foolish thoughts became foolishly spoken;
Like a potter molds clay, I got molded by my own nature;
I, foolish, grasped and lived.

Ati pida adharmthee, charachar suhu paamiya;
Tyaare bhakti dharm rishee, praktyaan kari diyaa.

Extreme suffering from unrighteousness, we have obtained companionship;
Then, by righteous devotion, the compassionate one has shown mercy.
